The National Youth Service Corps in Bayelsa State says it has mobilised 4, 364 corps members as INEC ad-hoc staff for the upcoming general elections. Spokesman of the corps the state,  Mathew Ngobua, disclosed this yesterday in Yenagoa. The INEC coordinator in the state, Mrs Omolayo Loto, had last week in a statement urged corps members to shun all  enticements from desperate politicians during the elections. Elections: NYSC ‘ll not disappoint the nation 2019 elections: Be unbiased — NYSC DG tells corps members 2019: NYSC seeks corps members’ safety